The management of the National Youth Service Corps (NYSC) has issued a statement debunking in totality the fake news making the rounds on certain blogs purporting that youth corps members serving in the northern part of the country are rather unsafe. The unfounded dis-news had made effort to misinform the members of the public with the false alarm that the NYSC management had issued a stay-indoor-instruction to the youth corps members for their safety, thus insinuating that lives were not safe in their service domain. Here below is the prompt statement issued by Mr Eddy Megwa, Director, Press and Public Relationson behalf of NYSC management totally debunking the unsubstantiated fabrication: “RE: …CORPS MEMBERS SERVING IN THE NORTH; STAY IN YOUR LODGES AND DON’T START WALKING ANYHOW OR TRAVEL FOR… “The attention of NYSC Management has been drawn to a fake news making the rounds on the social media, intended to instil fears in the minds of Corps Members, their parents and loved ones. “The originators of the news claimed that two Corps Members were shot dead at NYSC Secretariat, Jos, and other falsehoods “The management wishes to restate that nothing of such ever happened. The fabricators of the story are all out to cause mischief. “Accordingly, the general public, especially Corps Members are advised to disregard the fake news. POLL “The welfare of Corps Members shall continue to be accorded top priority by the National Youth Sevice Corps. “Mr Eddy MegwaDirector, Press and Public RelationsFor: Management.”